<br />I'm interested in your definition of "non relevant crap"?  I think there's a divergence of style, for sure.  Some like Nintendulator and FCEUX have all the stuff in one gargantuan window.  Others like NESICIDE have probably too many individual dockable windows containing singular pieces of debug information [like RAM, registers, etc.]  I did it that way, and arguably went too far to the extreme because people were complaining about having a gargantuan debug window with everything in it.

		

