		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">byuu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I wonder how the disassembler knows about the size of M when executing those two LDA # instructions.</div>
<br />The Apple II monitor (not GSBug, something far more primitive) saves "AXYPS", and the IIGS version also displays the new 65816 regs. The built-in disassembler probably disassembles based on the saved values of M and X bits in P.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
